RabbitMQ doesn't automatically propagate W3C `traceparent`/`tracestate` headers. You need to inject context on publish and extract it on consume.

**Publisher (Service A)** — inject the current trace context into message headers:

```csharp
using System.Diagnostics;

// Create an ActivitySource for your app
static readonly ActivitySource Source = new("ServiceA.Messaging");

// When publishing:
using var activity = Source.StartActivity("OrderEvent Publish", ActivityKind.Producer);

var props = channel.CreateBasicProperties();
props.Headers ??= new Dictionary<string, object>();

// Inject W3C trace context
if (Activity.Current != null)
{
    props.Headers["traceparent"] = Activity.Current.Id;           // W3C traceparent
    props.Headers["tracestate"]  = Activity.Current.TraceStateString ?? "";
}

channel.BasicPublish(exchange, routingKey, props, body);
```

**Consumer (Service B)** — extract context and start a linked activity:

```csharp
static readonly ActivitySource Source = new("ServiceB.Messaging");

// In your consumer callback:
void HandleMessage(BasicDeliverEventArgs ea)
{
    ActivityContext parentContext = default;

    if (ea.BasicProperties.Headers != null
        && ea.BasicProperties.Headers.TryGetValue("traceparent", out var raw))
    {
        var traceparent = Encoding.UTF8.GetString((byte[])raw);
        ActivityContext.TryParse(traceparent, null, out parentContext);
    }

    // This links the consumer span to the producer's trace
    using var activity = Source.StartActivity(
        "OrderEvent Process",
        ActivityKind.Consumer,
        parentContext);          // ← parent from the message header

    // … process the order …
}
```

**Wire it up in `Program.cs`** for both services:

```csharp
builder.Services.AddOpenTelemetry()
    .WithTracing(t => t
        .AddSource("ServiceA.Messaging")   // or ServiceB.Messaging
        .AddAspNetCoreInstrumentation()
        .AddOtlpExporter());               // Jaeger, Zipkin, etc.
```

**Why this works:** `Activity.Current.Id` is the W3C `traceparent` string (e.g. `00-<traceId>-<spanId>-01`). By passing it as a message header and parsing it on the consumer side as the `parentContext`, the consumer's span becomes a child of the producer's span — giving you one continuous trace across the queue.

**If you use MassTransit or NServiceBus** instead of raw `IModel`, both libraries do this injection/extraction automatically — you just need to register their diagnostic sources (e.g., `.AddSource("MassTransit")`).
